UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'In the novel *The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn* by Mark Twain, the young protagonist, Huck, embarks on a journey down the Mississippi River with Jim, a runaway slave.  Huck’s journey forces him to confront the injustices of slavery and to question the morality of the society in which he lives.  Huck’s experiences, as a young boy coming of age, challenge him to understand the complexities of race, friendship, and freedom in a rapidly changing world.  How, for instance, is the impact of Huck’s journey reflected in the novel?',
