  stimulus_text = 'The writer of a memoir is describing an event where a train is traveling across a bridge. The writer wants to emphasize how slowly the train was moving in order to create a sense of anticipation and suspense for the reader.  Which of the following sentences from the memoir is most effective at accomplishing this goal? Taken together, these details imply a broader principle that extends beyond the immediate example, though the author stops short of claiming universal proof. Readers must weigh both the evidence presented and the limits the author acknowledges.',
