UPDATE public.questions SET
  stimulus_text = 'The history of the development of computers is often told as a series of innovations, each building on the last.  However, that story is incomplete without considering the many women who made significant contributions to the field.  For example, Grace Hopper is credited with developing the first compiler, a program that translates human-readable code into machine-readable code.  Hopper’s invention made it possible for programmers to use high-level languages, which are easier to understand and use than low-level languages.  What is the most likely reason why the author includes the example of Grace Hopper?',
