  stimulus_text = 'A new study by the University of California, Berkeley, found that the effects of climate change are more severe in certain regions of the world.  The study''s authors, a team of climate scientists, report that the  Arctic is warming at twice the rate of the rest of the planet.  The study also found that the effects of climate change are more likely to be felt by people who live in coastal areas, due to rising sea levels and increased storm activity.  As a result of their findings, the authors recommend that governments take steps to mitigate the effects of climate change in these vulnerable regions.',
