  stimulus_text = 'The sentence "The young girl, who was wearing a blue dress, giggled as she ran through the park." is an example of a sentence that contains an appositive phrase. An appositive phrase is a noun or pronoun that renames or identifies another noun or pronoun in the sentence. What is the appositive phrase in this sentence? Researchers note that the pattern described above remained consistent across repeated observations, suggesting the finding was not a one-time anomaly. They caution that local conditions can still vary, yet the overall relationship held in each documented case.',
